Hi Naomi,

I hope everything is going well!

I heard you're moving house next month! That's such good news! I moved from China all the way to Japan, so I can definitely provide you with tons of advice!

Firstly, don't worry about living and making friends in a new area. When I came to Tokyo, I was so surprised by the locals' heart-warming welcome, and making friends was easy. You might even become one of the most popular students because of your unique identity—just be outgoing and make friends.

Secondly, living in a new area is a fresh experience. For example, you'll have new parks to explore and new shopping malls to visit. In my opinion, I see nearly no disadvantages to living in a new area.

However, there are some concerns about bullying in some circumstances. I almost got bullied because I was Chinese, but it all settled down, and everything is back on track again, so it isn't something you should worry about too much.

All in all, just relax. Everything will be fine, so look forward to your new journey!

